label.value: Lung Keratinizing Squamous Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A squamous cell lung carcinoma characterized by the presence of keratinization, pearl formation, and/or intercellular bridges.

label.value: Lung Non-Keratinizing Squamous Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A squamous cell lung carcinoma characterized by the absence of keratinization, pearl formation, and intercellular bridges.

label.value: Intercellular Bridges Present

value.value: A microscopic finding indicating the presence of intercellular bridges connecting adjacent cells in a tissue sample.

label.value: Lung Non-Mucinous Adenocarcinoma In Situ

value.value: Lung adenocarcinoma in situ characterized by the presence of type II pneumocyte and/or Clara cell differentiation. Almost all cases of lung adenocarcinoma in situ are non-mucinous.

label.value: Lung Mucinous Adenocarcinoma In Situ

value.value: A very rare lung adenocarcinoma in situ variant characterized by the presence of tall columnar cells with basal nuclei and abundant cytoplasmic mucin.

label.value: KISS1 Gene Product

value.value: A protein encoded by the KISS1 gene.

label.value: Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma In Situ

value.value: A preinvasive bronchial neoplastic lesion affecting the squamous epithelium. It is characterized by the absence of progression of maturation from base to luminal surface, basilar zone expansion with cellular crowding throughout the epithelium, absence of the intermediate zone, and surface flattening confined to the most superficial cells. The nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio is often high and variable, the chromatin is coarse and uneven, and mitotic figures are present through full thickness. The cell size may be markedly increased. Anisocytosis and pleomorphism may be present. (Adapted from WHO, 2015)

label.value: LIM Domain

value.value: The LIM domain is a zinc binding, cysteine rich motif consisting of two tandemly repeated zinc fingers. Unlike GATA type zinc fingers, LIM domains do not bind DNA but instead mediate protein-protein interactions. Functionally, LIM domain containing proteins have been implicated in cell lineage specification, cytoskeletal organization, and organ development.

label.value: NPY Gene Product

value.value: A protein encoded by the NPY gene.

label.value: Pro-Neuropeptide Y

value.value: Pro-neuropeptide Y (97 aa, ~11 kDa) is encoded by the human NPY gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of feeding behavior.

label.value: AGT Gene Product

value.value: A protein encoded by the human AGT gene.

label.value: Angiotensinogen

value.value: Angiotensinogen (485 aa, ~53 kDa) is encoded by the human AGT gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of blood pressure, body fluid and electrolyte homeostasis.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma of the Abdomen and Thoracic Visceral Organs TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma of the abdomen and thoracic visceral organs, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This classification system does not apply to desmoplastic small round cell tumor, epithelioid hemangioendothelioma, inflammatory myofibroblastic tumor, perivascular epithelioid cell tumor (PEComa), solitary fibrous tumor, gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST), uterine leiomyosarcoma, and retroperitoneal leiomyosarcoma.  This is a new classification system and there is no recommended prognostic stage grouping at this time. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: IDH1 R132H Negative

value.value: A finding indicating that a mutation of the IDH1 gene encoding the amino acid substitution Arg132His (R132H) in the isocitrate dehydrogenase [NADP] cytoplasmic protein has not been detected in a sample.

label.value: Proglucagon

value.value: Proglucagon  (180 aa, ~21 kDa) is encoded by the human GCG gene. This protein is involved in appetite, digestion, and glucose metabolism and homeostasis.
